Based on my exploration, I now have a complete picture of the architecture. Let me design a comprehensive implementation plan for adding a customizable Notes Section to the profile page.

## Implementation Plan: Profile Notes Section Feature

### Overview
This feature will add multiple customizable note containers to user profiles, using the existing Lexical editor inline, storing data in the `profile_layout` JSON column, and following established patterns from the codebase.

---

## Phase 1: Data Model & Backend

### 1.1 Update Backend Validation (Server Side)

**File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\services\uploadService.js`**

The `sanitizeProfileLayout()` function (lines 10-59) needs to handle a new `notes` array. Current structure validates only `sections`. Add notes validation:

**Data structure for notes:**
```javascript
{
  version: 1,
  preset: "classic",
  spacing: "md",
  radius: "lg",
  sections: [...],
  notes: [
    {
      id: "note_<uuid>",
      order: 0,
      content: "<lexical JSON state>",
      containerStyle: {
        bgColor: "#ffffff",
        borderColor: "#000000",
        borderWidth: 2,
        borderStyle: "solid",
        borderRadius: 8
      },
      fontColor: "#000000",
      fontFamily: "inherit",
      visible: true,
      created_at: "timestamp",
      updated_at: "timestamp"
    }
  ]
}
```

**Backend validation logic to add:**
- Limit to max 10 notes per profile
- Validate each note's content size (max 50KB JSON string)
- Sanitize containerStyle values (RGB/hex colors, numeric border values 0-10px, valid border styles)
- Ensure id format is `note_<uuid>`
- Validate fontFamily against allowed list or use "inherit"

### 1.2 Update Profile Layout Constants (Frontend)

**File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\utils\profileLayout\constants.js`**

Add constants for notes:
```javascript
export const MAX_NOTES_COUNT = 10;
export const DEFAULT_NOTE_CONTAINER_STYLE = {
  bgColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)",
  borderColor: "#888888",
  borderWidth: 1,
  borderStyle: "solid",
  borderRadius: 8
};
export const DEFAULT_NOTE_FONT_STYLE = {
  fontColor: "#000000",
  fontFamily: "inherit"
};
export const ALLOWED_BORDER_STYLES = ["solid", "dashed", "dotted", "double"];
export const ALLOWED_FONT_FAMILIES = [
  "inherit",
  "Arial",
  "Helvetica",
  "Times New Roman",
  "Georgia",
  "Courier New",
  "Verdana"
];
```

### 1.3 Update Profile Layout Normalization

**File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\utils\profileLayout\normalizeProfileLayout.js`**

Extend `normalizeProfileLayout()` function (lines 8-63) to handle notes array similar to how it handles sections. Add after line 60:

```javascript
// Normalize notes
const incomingNotes = Array.isArray(layout?.notes) ? layout.notes : [];
const normalizedNotes = [];

incomingNotes.forEach((note) => {
  if (!note?.id || !note.id.startsWith('note_')) return;
  if (normalizedNotes.length >= MAX_NOTES_COUNT) return;

  normalizedNotes.push({
    id: note.id,
    order: Number.isFinite(note?.order) ? note.order : normalizedNotes.length,
    content: note.content || null,
    containerStyle: {
      bgColor: note.containerStyle?.bgColor || DEFAULT_NOTE_CONTAINER_STYLE.bgColor,
      borderColor: note.containerStyle?.borderColor || DEFAULT_NOTE_CONTAINER_STYLE.borderColor,
      borderWidth: Number.isFinite(note.containerStyle?.borderWidth) 
        ? Math.min(10, Math.max(0, note.containerStyle.borderWidth))
        : DEFAULT_NOTE_CONTAINER_STYLE.borderWidth,
      borderStyle: ALLOWED_BORDER_STYLES.includes(note.containerStyle?.borderStyle)
        ? note.containerStyle.borderStyle
        : DEFAULT_NOTE_CONTAINER_STYLE.borderStyle,
      borderRadius: Number.isFinite(note.containerStyle?.borderRadius)
        ? Math.max(0, note.containerStyle.borderRadius)
        : DEFAULT_NOTE_CONTAINER_STYLE.borderRadius
    },
    fontColor: note.fontColor || DEFAULT_NOTE_FONT_STYLE.fontColor,
    fontFamily: ALLOWED_FONT_FAMILIES.includes(note.fontFamily)
      ? note.fontFamily
      : DEFAULT_NOTE_FONT_STYLE.fontFamily,
    visible: note.visible !== false,
    created_at: note.created_at || new Date().toISOString(),
    updated_at: note.updated_at || new Date().toISOString()
  });
});

normalized.notes = normalizedNotes;
```

